<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> hang all one’s bells on one horse • put all one’s eggs in one basket</xh5><p> <i>hang all one’s bells on one horse</i>—(UK arch.) leave all one’s property to one child: I’ll not <u>hang all my bells on one horse</u>. I’ll not leave all my property to one son.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>put all one’s money upon the wrong horse</b>—(also: put one’s money on a scratched horse) base one’s plans on a wrong guess about the result of smth.: Members will keenly feel the nature of the mistake when I say that we <u>put all our money upon the wrong horse</u>.</p><p> <i>put all one’s eggs in one basket—</i>allow all one’s hopes, money, etc. to depend on one event; risk everything at once: Personally, I prefer when at all possible not to <u>put all my eggs in one basket</u>, no matter how nice the basket.</p> </entry>
